GSG Wind, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
GSG Wind, LLC ("GSG") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the GSG Sublette and West Brooklyn facilities ("GSG Facilities").
The GSG Facilities are wind turbine generating facilities located in LaSalle and Lee Counties, Illinois. The GSG Facilities are interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth GSG's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service for each of the Sublette and West Brooklyn facilities. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
GSG's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to GSG shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT (Sublette): The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $125,125.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $10,427.08
TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT (West Brooklyn): The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $259,875.00 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $21,656.25
